{"_id":"p7OluVhxvPsFFYqd","name":"The Runepriest","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"class","data":{"name":"","description":"<h2>The Runepriest</h2>\n<p>Behind you, you can hear them arguing again - always, again and again, it&rsquo;s the same thing. The same words. Step back, listen. Do you hear it?</p>\n<p>The pattern, the code, the language, the words?</p>\n<p>Words have power. That&rsquo;s obvious to anyone who&rsquo;s lied or read a good book. Words are the force that move the civilized world. But even out here, you know that words change the world. Do you hear it yet?</p>\n<p>The scuffling of a goblin&rsquo;s foot is a word. The crackling fire of a dragon is a word. The divine will of the gods is a word. Step back. Listen.</p>\n<p>You hear it. And when you are ready, Runepriest, will you speak?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Names</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Dwarf: Durga, Khazad, Nain, Galenica, Telchar, Rachel, Annika, Sigrun, Reveka</li>\n<li>Human: Cypress, Abraham, Andel, Hob, Carmine, Elise, Ysold, Morgan, Uri</li>\n<li>Halfling: Dunstan, Rose, Ivy, Aubrey, Finnegan, Gaddock, Brigid, Cenn, Merry</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Look</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>BODY: Strong, Light, Hunched, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>EYES: Sharp, Glasses, Cloudy, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>CLOTHES: Scholar&rsquo;s robes, Holy habit, Common garb, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>HANDWRITING: Blocky, Delicate, Messy, or _ ___________</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Bonds</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>If words can&rsquo;t convince______________ of the truth, maybe actions will.</li>\n<li>I&rsquo;ve studied closely the work of _____________. We could teach each other a thing or two.</li>\n<li>______________&rsquo;s faith i s commendable, but mistaken. I can correct them.</li>\n<li>______________ and I will write our names i n history. __________________________________________________________</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Gear</h2>\n<p>You carry these but the words weigh more heavily:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Lexicon ( 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Chainmail ( 1 armor, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Dungeon Rations ( 5 uses, ration, 1 weight), Uses l eft: ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏</li>\n<li>5 coins</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose your hammer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Maul ( close, t wo-handed, +1 damage, 3 weight)</li>\n<li>Warhammer ( close, 1 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose two:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bag of Books ( 5 uses, 1 weight), Uses l eft: ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏</li>\n<li>Healing Potion ( 0 weight)</li>\n<li>Adventuring Gear (5 uses, 1 weight), Uses left: ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏ ❏</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>About The Runepriest</h2>\n<p>Moves</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Words of Power\n<ul>\n<li>This move intentionally permits a wide range of interpretations - the Runepriest and the GM should have a conversation about what kinds of limits or expectations to set around rune magic and Words of Power. This move asserts two specific qualities that affect the strength of rune magic - the medium for the writing and the means of inscription. My intuition is that quickly written or smaller runes, such as in ink, are less powerful, and that runes inscribed in harder, more magical material are stronger and last longer, but this is a suggestion only.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Interjection<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Aid or Interfere will still only trigger when appropriate - if the Runepriest&rsquo;s advice or other words aren&rsquo;t appropriate to aid (or interfere), then the move doesn&rsquo;t happen.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Fire and Brimstone<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The Runepriest must provide the GM with the precept/belief to which they are appealing.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>95 Theses<br />\n<ul>\n<li>In order for the move to trigger, the note does have to get back to its target somehow - but of course, it doesn&rsquo;t have to be the same note. The pope doesn&rsquo;t need to read the very letter you nail to the door, but can read someone&rsquo;s report about it.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Ghostwriter<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The phrase &ldquo;arcane materials&rdquo; is included here mostly with the intention to ask the player to describe how they are writing something metaphysically but also to color how many words of power one soul can hold/whether a soul can hold more than one or even one word of power without being destroyed.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Wise Man&rsquo;s Fear<br />\n<ul>\n<li>You can&rsquo;t say someone&rsquo;s true name that you don&rsquo;t know.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Hear My Voice<br />\n<ul>\n<li>In addition to the added complications of speaking words this way, the effect of Words of Power still depends upon the medium and means of inscription, which is to say that air counts as the medium and material, for the purposes of determining the effect. Again, the effects are left up to conversation between GM and player.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Future Tense<br />\n<ul>\n<li>When working with triggered runes, it&rsquo;s up to the GM&rsquo;s preference as to whether the roll for Words of Power happens when the rune is scribed or when it&rsquo;s activated. However, describing the intended effect (and thus, whether the rune has a delayed trigger or not) always happens b efore the roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Rest is Silence<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The new rune is likely in some way related to the deceased&rsquo;s powers and deeds in life.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Spells</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Doom<br />\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;As written, this does nothing for GM characters and messes with the Barbarian&rsquo;s Herculean Appetites. For the first fix, the GM can interpret what fictional effect the spell might have that empowers a GM character against another character. For the Barbarian, if Herculean Appetites triggers, their player can choose to roll a third die, either a d6 or d8, but their final total must include a d6 and a d8.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Shibboleth<br />\n<ul>\n<li>This spell supersedes Tongue and Mouth of the Rune Keeper.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Celestial Bolt<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Found wanting by the Divine, that is. This can include the Runepriest. Especially devout or divinely beloved creatures might take no damage from this spell.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Summon Angel<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The extraplanar creature is summoned believing the Runepriest to be worthy - the Runepriest&rsquo;s actions or words might convince the creature otherwise.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","races":{"0":{"label":"Dwarf","description":"Stonework is a major part of your studies. You know the rune for Earth in addition to your other two runes."},"1":{"label":"Human","description":"You're a scholar and explorer, familiar with many l esser runes. Choose a l evel 1 spell from any playbook - it’s a Runepriest spell for you."},"2":{"label":"Halfling","description":"Although you serve all divinity, you are especially close to one god. Name them. You gain the Cleric move D ivine Guidance.\nYour god’s Petition i s related to the runes you know."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"alignments":{"0":{"label":"Neutral","description":"Learn a truth of the gods or their language."},"1":{"label":"Good","description":"Resolve conflict peacefully through words."},"2":{"label":"???","description":""}},"equipment":{"0":{"label":"You carry these but the words weigh more heavily:","mode":"checkbox","items":["hOirByy8R5RTFXOd","ic5dH6aNzBgEuTjA","6JcOoZ8CNqYxLgyQ"]},"1":{"label":"Choose your hammer:","mode":"radio","items":["fvtXSG3oibD5SuIP","jNnBRnlV90jBquwW"]},"2":{"label":"Choose two:","mode":"checkbox","items":["YwHV7WYzTPSAOorl","CMhNmAwhLVZk9lfq","iaxOPwJIrsnzGJWr"]}},"hp":6,"load":8,"damage":"d6"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Lexicon","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Lexicon</p>\n<p>You have mastered several spells, made of smaller words of power, and inscribed them in your lexicon.</p>\n<p>You start out with three first l evel spells.</p>\n<p>Whenever you gain a l evel, you i nscribe a new spell of your l evel or l ower. Your lexicon is 1 weight.</p>","class":"The Runepriest","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pKoevTP3bWgnwdsy"}
{"_id":"sB6DlQCwlw4zugr1","name":"Words Of Power","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Words Of Power (WIS)</p>\n<p>You have studied the divine l anguage that created the world, and have learned two runes.</p>\n<p>When you inscribe a rune you know onto an object and will it to power, roll+WIS.</p>\n<p>On a hit, say what property aligned with that rune you i nstill upon the object for a time; a shield i nured to Death could protect against spirits, a horn imbued with Water pours freely, an arrow i nscribed with Sky might fly on i ts own.</p>\n<p>The strength of the effect depends on the strength of the material and method of i nscription - The GM will tell you the effect you produce based on the size and details of your i nscription, and how l ong i t will last based on the material.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, the effect l asts until the rune i s defaced or the magic of the material runs out.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, the effect i s fleeting, dangerous, or weak, your choice.</p>","class":"The Runepriest","rollType":"WIS","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vRRPrk3B8WrSXhF7","name":"Etherealness","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"spell","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Etherealness</p>\n<p>7th Level - Ongoing</p>\n<p>You turn intangible and pass i nto the boundary between worlds.</p>\n<p>While you are ethereal, you can&rsquo;t be perceived by or be interacted with by material things, unless they have been enchanted i n some way. However, you also cannot affect in any way non-ethereal entities.</p>\n<p><strong>While this spell i s ongoing, you can&rsquo;t cast a spell.</strong></p>","spellLevel":7,"rollFormula":"","prepared":false,"class":"The Runepriest"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
